  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I write answer in engineering exams in English being gujrati medium student?",
  "response": "Writing answers in English for engineering exams can be challenging, especially if you are more comfortable with Gujarati. However, with practice and some strategies, you can improve your ability to express your knowledge effectively. Here are some tips to help you:\n\n1. **Understand the Concepts**: Make sure you have a clear understanding of the engineering concepts in your native language first. This will help you translate your thoughts into English more easily.\n\n2. **Use Simple Language**: Start by using simple English sentences. Focus on conveying your ideas clearly rather than using complex vocabulary.\n\n3. **Practice Writing**: Regularly practice writing answers in English. You can take previous exam questions and write your answers in English. This will help you get comfortable with the language.\n\n4. **Learn Key Terminology**: Familiarize yourself with key engineering terms in English. Create a glossary of important words and phrases related to your subjects.\n\n5. **Structure Your Answers**: Use a clear structure for your answers:\n   - **Introduction**: Briefly introduce the topic or question.\n   - **Body**: Explain your reasoning, calculations, or processes step by step.\n   - **Conclusion**: Summarize your findings or the main points of your answer.\n\n6. **Use Diagrams and Equations**: In engineering, diagrams and equations can convey a lot of information. Label them clearly in English, and refer to them in your text.\n\n7. **Practice Past Papers**: Go through past exam papers and try answering them in English. This will help you get a sense of the exam format and the type of language used.\n\n8. **Seek Feedback**: If possible, ask teachers or classmates who are proficient in English to review your answers and provide feedback.\n\n9. **Learn from Others**: Read textbooks, articles, and papers in English to see how concepts are explained. This will help you get used to the language and style used in engineering.\n\n10. **Stay Calm During Exams**: During the exam, take a moment to organize your thoughts before you start writing. If you feel stuck, try to articulate your ideas in Gujarati first, then translate them into English.\n\nBy following these tips and consistently practicing, you will become more comfortable writing in English for your engineering exams. Good luck!",
